criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of at least three non-carious cervical lesions on the buccal aspect of
             previous vital teeth or premolars;

          -  Visible plaque index presence and / or gingival bleeding index of at most 20%;

          -  Probing depth of at least 3 mm in the experimental site and / or buccal 4 mm in any
             place;

          -  Patients with good general health condition;

          -  Patients able to understand and sign the letter of information and the free and
             informed consent;

          -  Patients willing to return every six months to revaluation queries.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of less than 20 teeth in the mouth;

          -  Patients undergoing orthodontic treatment;

          -  Patients with occlusion problems;

          -  Veneers with wear over 50% of the incisal / occlusal structure;

          -  Absence of tooth antagonist.
